QWAhgHe=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3moHnp62tq5AI_G92p6Nl-2XHXJzf5cvgkp0dZi1vqmSiWik6XN338t-fsi-TkRYcQDERzkGH6o8kKyuoK4oeptshVGzZH7K3bYy8iP7vO_tjrJgIwAjw1fNZ0PuT9O_JgIHfwQXSfLN0=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1YdtKXsQ0vX0TD778FbO5vz7ajlvaJUEkbt9Tjvghasa3o3Y2tJPlSP82y8WAt2PUse5fKiAs-UwsMDpw0Q8JWyMkCluMfC5XyOMbGOVSoReq7P638r6U8sRDAXGYmgxmkOAf1m2z8UiNm=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2q-VQIemgcT9dfYZCcNkW-6Eo31GuOdSO26L1KBuaL2Y_I95P-0zdVVRKmNgnA2xrzNKzzulOnEoDpmZq6PnsHQcrEUCAOFDzT6D-zuxGw59tIrCX5Zkv4FdxRKDt0xqnVr0xaNBG3CrJN=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn103RWGAW_8uEhedFVkl1LemnaWxrSYXd_ZR5X1HAqufzbFYJiqC7y8uV3KqD7P9UGjFMLDtlzkGdGs2AvB9gxw9s-UujAe29GiMpu5_uWBhd8Tmc9xADSdWYOW-iN-0wx_WIn39ia7Adk2=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-31"},{"Name":"Kimberly Slater","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURC-wXVoMrh8mxL0h8bSOHbQJoPNWN30Kn-Sj_Ir5dTnriGphP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had a very disappointing experience with Nick from Mister Sparky.\n\nI originally scheduled an appointment simply to have a ceiling fan installed. The fan was already assembled and just needed to be mounted and wired. When Nick arrived, he said he needed to perform a full home electrical evaluation first, which I was fine with.\n\nHowever, after looking at the panel, he began making alarming statements like, “I’m surprised the breaker isn’t constantly shorting out,” and “It’s not if, but when this causes a major problem.” I was in the middle of work, so I called my husband so he could speak with him directly. We were then told the panel was in very bad shape and needed immediate replacement.\n\nNick sent over three options: $24,000, $15,000, and $11,000 — stating the $11,000 option would “just make the home safe.” The urgency and tone felt extremely high-pressure. When we said we wanted a second opinion, he appeared offended and made comments like, “We are the best,” “We wouldn’t be in business if we overcharged,” and even compared it to questioning a doctor recommending a heart transplant. (Yes, I absolutely would get a second opinion in that situation.) When I mentioned my uncle is a master electrician, he responded, “Then why isn’t he here to install your fan?” Because he was out of town and I didn't want him to go out of his way to just put up a fan.\n\nAfter declining the panel work, I asked for the price to simply install the fan — it was nearly $600.\n\nFor context, I work in real estate and review inspection reports regularly, including electrical panels that genuinely need replacement. I have never seen numbers that high. That raised serious red flags.\n\nI contacted one of our trusted electricians, who I should have called first but didn't want to waste his time with something so simple he is very busy. He came out within 30 minutes of Nick leaving, thoroughly inspected everything, and confirmed there was absolutely nothing wrong with our panel. He is a two-time master electrician and electrical engineer, so I trust his expertise. He installed the fan for $100 in under 20 minutes and even serviced the panel for peace of mind.\n\nThe entire experience felt unnecessarily alarming and high-pressure. I checked reviews before booking and was surprised given how positive they were. Unfortunately, this was not our experience at all. I would strongly recommend getting a second opinion before committing to any major electrical work. And I would not have Mister Sparky be your first, second or third choice!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heather Mason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_NjO-KLf9IepjUXmGwW6Z1rptrBCn6bX3Xgkwm8ycBTupcvov=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big thanks to Jasyn for the great work on my home this week. He paid special attention to detail on every project, making sure it was done how I wanted it. He informed me every step of the way so I could make the best decisions. My house is more comfortable now because of him and I love the new pendant lights in my kitchen especially!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3m3M5pZjhuNGcI1b1oFggAC22dG1vm66k5oB3McoTUr8SJt8hcjE2IwBD6xYYMpdlcMBk4QJM92uFZWGKhGc_o65naz4Uj8dmXNLXYlZji46p2bRfy_lRzjBsLeWkCjpawwnfkZeIj91oO=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-21"},{"Name":"Parker Woods","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKj5lpzfZA8dN2h111VFIw3GF6GVI5QL5dtMm4jp6bs2nekhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really appreciated Nathan’s and Gianna’s efforts to install a new electrical panel and perform other electrical work in my home. Their extensive knowledge of best practices reflected their dedication to craftsmanship and customer service, including friendliness, professionalism, prompt arrival times, was fantastic!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3kHl4G4PQcG3yGThyg5VYiktHmecKHjpBk6Al8uTojFSGdm0fBYyXyx-clDQKRAYJwXNmAKLSfTBuVaEEvflXIY0-DgY88p6e-OrgnYPxUbHt8NmlOBkQp1ErsgSBcM8mEOyPDjZbcWp8=k-no"],"When":"2026-3-2"},{"Name":"Kate Eppen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIIm9ygGnId8rCzYebwVi3vEt3fS_a2OSO0HiavzGZeeetpCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cory was amazing! Super thorough and thoughtful. Gave us lots of options and made us feel very informed and comfortable with our choices. Would highly recommend Mr. Sparky - and especially Cory!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn09z6cZw5cLAFePNhu68jZt_hD7F5CyXpvxrZLH958FeQIEQki6Xd60PQQ-MfWBehemrFslB6y_rlnnO-8kv1sWeKazE1YL14jMF0nE9A2orgQtQHBKjmATTgqlOTzsZgERSwyvlnnLTUB0=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-16"},{"Name":"Nik Brauer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSTQA23tf8UJlPy_q3XUYyjzqsXAqqFPvsILjU_ZD-TRliVG8y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The installer did an A+ job. Probably could have done it for cheaper if I had been willing to call around, but for quality work done on time I’m happy.\n\nI did not expect the first person to visit my house, who was very nice and professional, was not the person who actually did the work but more of a quote guy. Be aware there is a bit of a ‘jiffy lube’ dynamic where they will try to up sell you on panel maintenance and whatnot.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
