ad on 5 gallons of gas.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0-byiZXn4L6FPp0gGigBf2kXa-nMckMIxT9lIVMpKGByfRagG6ib8YQYyNPhQ-e60SvXlzosM74u0JR-aQ0inz5JtAgjH0gfgM8EX7zIeRzTwPlSno6wZ9UMzcaG5m3m0Cxufq=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0jFaEMwDBXzrwOdC_iOjY8ULg4nxG5YnwtE2XlCzfTbSxEZ0xZj67zsjA7f6GpsWaHteyBPw1pBmUSMa5Fzo4CfXDpxjBqpf8a22RHEjkhvqDUtsJp195cRLkir3qP4p-bByMj=k-no"],"When":"2023-9-7"},{"Name":"Lori Paquette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIAQsvlDbyaIJBtH7Rv8ORJbJ16ImyCaSaXV-fDBiEI5UPhxw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"0 stars-I don’t write reviews but buyer beware-got a builder quote (they used to be reputable years ago), to install a garage fixture 18’ high, and change out 6 outlet covers. To arrive Monday 10am-no show, no call, secretary says truck breakdown, after having waited til 1 no call-promised on the way-no show-promises first on Wednesday-this time secretary says she sees driver getting in truck to head to home-no show-promises on the way-then another technician to arrive noon-he shows at 12:45 has no idea what he’s to do and only one person-no ladder for the height-says will put covers although light fixture was first important to do-takes 2 hours and charges $415! Stressed first time pregnant daughter  after no shows, lies, and demanding more than double for easy work-I call the owner, who suggested will review. I get a copy of invoice that says 2 technicians worked and charged labor almost $300 plus they charged over $150 for material!! But they gave little discount for her troubles! Of course the owner never calls back after several attempts-so now the major work the fixture still needs to be installed-never again-and you lost a very large project coming up-\nRUN if you don’t want double the costs and repeated no shows-they advertise on the truck on time! And they could care less they stressed out a 7 month pregnant in 106 degree weather-this owner and secretary will lie to your face-be warned.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cristian Arce-Bustos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6HbUSrsgy7NN58528BzkLV3_8IU77B4CEJCUKJKNvBmX3NA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing service by an amazing company. I could not be more pleased with the quickness, helpfulness, \u0026 knowledge that I received. They responded quickly to my situation and helped get everything fixed during this emergency. They are great down to earth people who I like having in my home doing the work. Coudln't say enough good about Dunman Electric. I appreciate their service and will use them for years to come.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tami Bailey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWM6D62D4fI9PsV58_C_pUw7endiZbkx4CJI0L-PmPrjabfQWjK1g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Completely unprofessional.  Hired them to install appropriate CAT cable to an upstairs office that would work with our Google Fiber mesh network and increase speeds to the hardwired room.  First of all, technician arrived 3 hours LATE with no advance notice.  Technician seemed clueless on how to solution my request.  Ultimately, his recommended solution was to install a CAT6.  It took him almost and hour to come up with the solution.  Upon installation, we immediately saw a negative impacted to our network speeds.  These guys did a shotty job. Lead technician had a poor attitude and honestly didn't seem educated enough for the job.  On top of everything, Dunman marked up the CAT6 conduit ten times the retail price, charged me 4 hours labor x 2 technicians (1 was a trainee) for a job that should have taken \u003c30mins.  They charged me $642.20 just for LABOR!!  THEN, Dunman Billed my credit card for $1055.50, without authorization, EVEN after I indicated to them (IN WRITING) that I did not agree with their invoice. Overall, a horrible experience and wouldn't recommend you doing business with the dishonest company.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dan L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbUOgUwt_abJHnNXbUGF_Gsi8WAH_kIeFRNuJzFJlqpK72DQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot say enough nice things about the quality and professionalism I've experienced from Dunman.  Josh has done work on 3 separate occasions for my kitchen remodel and has been great to work with.  Becky has always been able to fit me into their calendar at short notice and their prices are very fair.  Wish I could say the same about my other contractors, but quality is hard to come by lately.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
