ut time some lobbying happens to remove this monopolization and open up options for us living here.\n\nThey know if this happened, they'd immediately lose half of their customer base.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mohammad Raeisy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiV9QSadD65fSvXV3ylMsbvMCnBGsavOcHrJP-LZHPA3lMVaw8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"After 35 days of requesting the removal of the electricity meter for repairs and to secure the home's electrical system, and after numerous calls and submitted requests, no action has been taken. The services and commitment of their staff to the public are truly poor and insulting.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ean Karabanoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGaPeO77fRVpWEWpgOHKAXyqGfaL6OYXZQrY3WBO_hrUKIRtQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This company feels like a huge scam. Right after signing up with them, I got a new card from my bank because I had a faulty chip. I forgot to update my card in their system and I received no calls and no emails from the company letting me know my payments failed to go through. All I got was a letter in the mail letting me know my account was “cash only\npayments” because the payments failed. Now I have to pay cash only for 12 months unless my banks writes them a letter. Total trash organization.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jade Green","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKy90izWcNDcd6jtOYe9y-KOywSOuYVuX3BWRipnAhHpBngLA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"relentless as only a monopoly could be. On a payment plan and pay your bill ONE DAY late?  DISCONNECTION NOTICE!  This is really how this company does business? disgraceful, inhumane, despicable. God forbid I have other things going on in my life like working 60-hour weeks to pay their exorbitant tiered rip-off system plus don't forget the extra $30 tacked on to every bill for \"trash, community,\" and other various fees, even though I already pay those to my apartment community AND THRU MY TAXES","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Miranda Rogers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJE7HqQLZx1P3qmJupUa7mCiV5djqvNbTMpvvp3WaES2Dk18Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They charge you for waste services whether you want it or not. I only wanted to set up electricity, I don't need someone to take out my garbage for me. It should be an optional service, especially when I'm already paying trash services at the apartment complex! Furthermore, the trash can has its own fee, and -- no -- you can't use your own.\n\nThis company is dishonest and immoral, and their actions should be considered criminal. They duplicated my service fees, but never sent me a single bill. I had been paying my services without fail on time, and then months after moving found out all that money I paid them was being charged to me again. They refused to work with me or remove it from my credit as a derogatory mark. Since they are the only place in Austin where you can obtain electricity for an apartment, they can basically do whatever they want--and they do. They will tell you they don't care, and they won't even try to fix their own errors.\n\nIf you can, rent in Round Rock; there are multiple options in that jurisdiction. You'll probably end up saving hundreds of dollars, even if you pay more for gas to drive further to work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michele Keller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTyp0pHFgmDK_zx3KKB5Vt1M_ouXGIc9OLU3S_ayHEP4K7PZI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have had electricity with them for 3 years, From first months bill to the very last there have been issues!! First 3 months bills were 500.00 for a 2/2 apt 890 sq ft. I am very frugal with my AC, 75 at night and off during the day. I ran my AC 2 to 4 months out of the year and still didn't have a bill that wasn't 200.00 /mo at the least. I called and requested they check my meter, City of Austin blames my apt complex, apt complex blames City of Austin. My apt complex was nice enough to replace the whole AC unit and thermostat which had no impact on the bill. HORRIBLE customer service!! Had my electricity turned off for the first time EVER in my life for a past due balance that was being disputed. NO notification prior to disconnect that it was going to be disconnected. LAST bill comes in which should reflect a 200.00 deposit refund. It doesn't it reflects 0.00 and i can't get them to adjust it or refund my money or explain mathematically my last bill. I was told a supervisor would call me in 24 to 48 hrs. This was after calling all morning to get a busy signal, then 20 minutes on hold to get a representative, then placed on hold back and forth for another 45 minutes with no resolve. DO NOT USE THEM IF YOU DO NOT HAVE TO!!!!!!!!!!!!!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
